Troubleshooting Tips
Database Connection Errors:

Verify database file exists in data/ directory
Check file permissions: chmod 644 data/security_culture.db
Ensure SQLite3 is installed: sudo apt install sqlite3
Flask Application Not Starting:

Confirm virtual environment is activated
Check port 5000 is not in use: lsof -i :5000
Verify all dependencies installed: pip list
D3.js Visualizations Not Rendering:

Check browser console for JavaScript errors
Verify API endpoints return valid JSON
Ensure D3.js library loads correctly (check network tab)
Empty or Missing Data:

Run generate_sample_data.py again
Verify database tables created successfully
Check date ranges in analysis functions
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated how to build a comprehensive security culture measurement system. You learned to collect metrics across multiple dimensions (training, phishing, incidents, surveys), analyze trends over time, and visualize results through an interactive dashboard. These skills are essential for security awareness program management and demonstrating the effectiveness of security initiatives to stakeholders.

Key takeaways:

Security culture requires multi-dimensional measurement
Trend analysis reveals program effectiveness over time
Visualization makes complex data accessible to decision-makers
Continuous monitoring enables proactive interventions
Continue practicing by extending the system with additional metrics, implementing alerting for concerning trends, or integrating with real organizational data sources.
